    <item>
      <title>Christian Definition</title>
      <link>/docs/gospel-messages/christian_definitioin/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 10 Apr 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/docs/gospel-messages/christian_definitioin/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The original Greek word for Christian is “Christianos” which comes from the two Greek words “Christ and tian.” The word Christ means “anointed” and tian means “little.” So the word “Christian” literally means “little anointed ones.” During his life Jesus was called the “messiah” which meant “the anointed one” and we are his “little anointed ones” who have been anointed by his Holy Spirit to represent Him in this world.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
